So kpod load is not actually pulling the image again, it correctly loads the image from the tar file. The print statement is what is misleading. Basically what happens is, when it detects the transport is of docker-archive or oci-archive, it opens up the tar files and reads the image name from the manifest stored inside, which is what is printed in the statement "Trying to print ..." as the image name stored in the tar file is of the form "registry.com/image:tag".
I can fix this to print the file name instead when loading or we can follow what docker does and just print something like `Loaded image: docker.io/alpine:latest` at the end.
@rhatdan what do you think?
